OOP Implementation:

Encapsulates all file operations in a FileProcessor class

Methods for each operation (read, modify, write)

Proper separation of concerns

Error Handling:

Comprehensive exception handling for common file operations

Specific error messages for different failure modes

Graceful degradation when errors occur

Flexibility:

Supports custom modification functions

Automatic output file naming

Can be used programmatically or via user input

Best Practices:

Input validation

Context managers for file operations

Clear documentation

Default behaviors with override options
